      "writtenOn": "2021-05-07T02:11:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I feel that syncing the sequence between Group() and pollReplicas() via resume and cancel() can be racy. As I said in an above comment, there is no guarantee that this go routine will see the up-to-date copy of resume when Group exited. It can protected with a mutex, but I think it\u0027d be safer to invoke Group() in a goroutine, and handles the exit condition in the main goroutine directly.\n\n```\nvar wg sync.WaitGroup\nreplicas :\u003d replicasFunc()\nr :\u003d replicas\n\nfor {\n    groupCtx, groupCancel :\u003d context.WithCancel(ctx)\n    wg.Add(1)\n    go func() {\n        defer wg.Done()\n        Group(....)\n    }\n\n    for ;r \u003d\u003d replicas; {\n        select {\n        case \u003c-time.After(30 * time.Second):\n           r \u003d replicasFunc()\n        case \u003c-ctx.Done():\n           wg.Wait()\n           return\n        }\n   }\n   groupCancel()\n   wg.Wait()\n   replicas \u003d r\n}\n```",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 61,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 78,
        "endChar": 0
      },
      "revId": "42c1261fe920d61cb78874c1f74e1262c6809bce",
