      "writtenOn": "2021-05-07T02:10:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t think all changes are good.\n\nBad ones:\n1. panicing at the start of the cron process was OK-ish, because a new process would be auto-deployed by k8s, effectively doing a retry.\n   OTOH, the new function can accidentally panic some cron-unrelated code, yet would look just fine at callsite, so code reviewers are unlikely to notice this.\n\n2. Cancelled context results in Shards constant?\nIt\u0027s non unusual to have several contexts in 1 go function (e.g. temp inner constant with short lifetime), whereby this func can be called with already cancelled context (prob. by mistake), yet the rest of the caller continues working with not-yet-canceled context and everything will look fine.\n\n\nGood one:\nHandling `spanutil.ErrNoResults` case specifically.\n\nSo, how about\n\n    // CurrentMaxShard returns the highest shard id in the Invocations table,\n    // or the Shards constant if table is empty.\n    CurrentMaxShard(ctx context.Context) (int, error)\n\n\nThen, the cron func can handle errors this way:\n  * on first CurrentMaxShard call, panic (as before)\n  * on refreshes, treat error as transient and retry after some time",
      "revId": "42c1261fe920d61cb78874c1f74e1262c6809bce",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
